    "where μt|t = μt|t-1 + Kt (y t -H μt|t-1), Σt|t = (I -Kt H) Σt|t-1 and Kt is an estimate of the Kalman gain, that is",
    "Although (11) can be sampled from trivially, it is common to perform a stochastic update step (see e.g.",
    "Katzfuss et al., 2016), which moves ensemble members according to a Gaussian pseudoobservation ỹj t ∼ N (H xj t, R).",
    "New ensemble members are obtained as x j t = xj t + Kt (y t -ỹj t) which avoids draws of dimension d x (with d x >> d y in common applications).",
